Usage: setPinDensityMapMode [-help] [-reset] [-displayStep <step_value>]
                            [-threshold <density>] [-gridInMicron micron | -gridInRow nrRow]

-help                                # Prints out the command usage
-reset                               # Resets all or specified options to default value
-displayStep <step_value>            # range step for displaying the pin
                                     # density map (float, default=0.05)
-gridInMicron <micron>               # specify the value (in micron) of side of
                                     # square grid for pin density
                                     # calculations.
                                     # (float, default=50, min=0, max=1000)
-gridInRow <nrRow>                   # specify the value (in row-height) of
                                     # side of square grid for pin density
                                     # calculations.
                                     # (int, default=10, min=1, max=100)
-threshold <density>                 # threshold value over which the densities
                                     # must be reported. (float, default=0.5)